// About.astro - Short intro about me and why this program exists
---

<section id="about" class="py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-16 scroll-animate">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Guiding People Into Their Tech Careers
        </h2>
        <div class="w-20 h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-violet-600 mx-auto rounded-full"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div class="space-y-6 scroll-animate">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Over the years, I've helped a diverse group of people break into software engineering â€”
            career changers from fields like teaching and accounting, university graduates looking for
            their first tech role, and students just beginning their professional journey.
          </p>

          <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Now I'm formalizing this experience into a structured mentorship program. Whether you're
            switching careers or starting fresh, you'll get a clear roadmap from learning fundamentals
            to landing your first software engineering role.
          </p>

          <div class="relative bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-violet-50 p-6 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-blue-600 shadow-sm">
            <svg class="absolute top-4 right-4 w-8 h-8 text-blue-200" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M14.017 21v-7.391c0-5.704 3.731-9.57 8.983-10.609l.995 2.151c-2.432.917-3.995 3.638-3.995 5.849h4v10h-9.983zm-14.017 0v-7.391c0-5.704 3.748-9.57 9-10.609l.996 2.151c-2.433.917-3.996 3.638-3.996 5.849h3.983v10h-9.983z"/>
            </svg>
            <p class="text-gray-800 font-medium italic relative z-10">
              "Starting a tech career doesn't have to be overwhelming. With the right guidance and
              a clear path, anyone can succeed in software engineering."
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

